{
  "doc_id": "15400",
  "text": "Several authors have compared different airway anesthesia techniques. In 1990, Webb et al. [CITATION_1] compared trans-cricoid lignocaine injection with use of the spray-as-you-go technique for awake fiberoptic bronchoscopy in 70 adult patients. In 1992, Graham et al. [CITATION_2] compared three different methods of providing airway anesthesia during fiberoptic bronchoscopy in 53 patients. In 2000, Kundra et al. [CITATION_3] compared nebulized lignocaine 4% with combined regional nerve block for awake fiberoptic nasotracheal intubation in 48 adult patients.",
